After the signing of this agreement, Mauritania became a democratic country and Mohammed Abdul Aziz became the prime minister of this country. Despite being home to numerous cultures and beliefs, Mauritania follows the majority ruled government. Mauritania is regarded as one of the fourteen countries of the world that are ruled by aristocracy. The Gautiers are considered to be the royal family of Mauritania. This country was still a monarchy as of 2007 and André Bothain was the prime minister of this country.
